Content Management Integration – Java ↔ Payload (Locked Specification)

Scope

This document fully locks item 7: Communication with Payload.

It defines:
	•	The chosen integration architecture (Java as middleware)
	•	The “safe API” strategy
	•	Which content lives in Payload
	•	Which fields are editable from Merchant Admin
	•	Roles & permissions for content editing
	•	Read/write flows for Public Site and Merchant Admin

This specification is implementation-ready and aligned with previously locked decisions.

⸻

1. Core Decision (Locked)

1.1 Java acts as the sole middleware to Payload
	•	Merchant Admin never talks directly to Payload
	•	Public site never talks directly to Payload
	•	Java exposes explicit, allowlisted endpoints
	•	Java calls Payload using a service account

This provides:
	•	Strong tenant isolation
	•	Field-level control
	•	Auditing and observability
	•	Freedom to replace Payload later without breaking the frontend

⸻

2. Architecture Overview

Merchant Admin (React SPA)
        |
        v
Java Backend (Content Gateway module)
        |
        v
Payload CMS

The Content Gateway is a dedicated Java module responsible only for content operations.

⸻

3. Safe API Strategy (Locked)

3.1 Explicit allowlist only
	•	No generic “proxy” or “pass-through” endpoints
	•	Every field writable from Merchant Admin is explicitly mapped in Java DTOs

3.2 Tenant scope enforced in Java
	•	Every Payload read/write includes tenantId
	•	Client cannot supply or override tenantId

3.3 Payload service account
	•	Java authenticates to Payload using a single service credential
	•	Credential is stored securely (env/secret store)
	•	No Payload credentials are ever exposed to the client

3.4 Auditing
	•	All content mutations are logged in the platform DB
	•	Includes tenantId, userId, action, timestamp, and changed fields

⸻

4. Payload Data Model (MVP – Locked)

4.1 tenant_site_settings (Singleton per tenant)

Type: Payload Collection (not Global)

Uniqueness: One document per tenantId

Editable from Merchant Admin (EDITOR + ADMIN)
	•	business_display_name
	•	logo (media reference)
	•	primary_color
	•	secondary_color (optional)
	•	contact:
	•	phone
	•	email
	•	address
	•	whatsapp
	•	business_hours_text
	•	social_links:
	•	instagram
	•	facebook
	•	tiktok
	•	header:
	•	navigation_items (simple list)
	•	footer:
	•	footer_text
	•	footer_links
	•	seo_defaults:
	•	site_title
	•	meta_description
	•	og_image

Not editable from Merchant Admin
	•	tenantId
	•	template selection
	•	plan flags
	•	custom scripts / HTML

⸻

4.2 tenant_pages

Type: Payload Collection

Uniqueness: One document per (tenantId, pageType)

Page types (MVP)
	•	HOME
	•	ABOUT
	•	CONTACT
	•	FAQ (optional)

Editable fields (EDITOR + ADMIN)
Each page uses a guided, form-based schema:
	•	hero:
	•	title
	•	subtitle
	•	image
	•	primary_cta_text
	•	primary_cta_link
	•	sections (limited set):
	•	rich_text
	•	image_text
	•	feature_list
	•	testimonials (simple)
	•	seo:
	•	meta_title
	•	meta_description
	•	og_image

Explicitly excluded
	•	Arbitrary block builders
	•	Custom HTML/CSS
	•	Free-form layout editing

